aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription: Pay each overdue premium with interest at the rate of 7% per year from its due date
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLIRuleEngine) (Def Version:1) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFAmountWithCalculatedCurrency) var AnnualInterest : Num8 var debug : Pointer var BillLinePeriod : Num8 var InterestOnPeriod : Num8 var MonthOnPeriod : Num8 var MonthOnQuater : Num8 var MonthOnSemiAnnual : Num8 var MonthOnAnnual : Num8 var BeginDate : tWFDate var EndDate : tWFDate var BillLineAmount : Num8
MonthOnQuater = 3.0 MonthOnSemiAnnual = 6.0 MonthOnAnnual = 12.0 AnnualInterest = 0.07 ; ;debug = Risky.OpenDebug ; BillLineAmount = self.BillLine__BaseAmount BeginDate = self.BillLine__EffectiveDate EndDate = self.BillLine__EndDate MonthOnPeriod = self.NumberOfMonthBetweenTwoDates(BeginDate, EndDate) ; Result = 0 if not self.DateIsNull(EndDate) if MonthOnPeriod < 1 ; Monthly InterestOnPeriod = self.Power(1 + AnnualInterest, 1.0 / 12.0) - 1 Result = self.BillLine__BaseAmount * self.Power(1 + InterestOnPeriod, self.NumberOfMonthBetweenTwoDates(BeginDate, self.CurrentDate)) - self.BillLine__BaseAmount else if MonthOnPeriod < MonthOnQuater ; Quaterly InterestOnPeriod = self.Power(1 + AnnualInterest, 1.0 / 4.0) - 1 Result = self.BillLine__BaseAmount * self.Power(1 + InterestOnPeriod, self.NumberOfMonthBetweenTwoDates(BeginDate, self.CurrentDate) / MonthOnQuater) - self.BillLine__BaseAmount else if MonthOnPeriod < MonthOnSemiAnnual ; Semi-Annually InterestOnPeriod = self.Power(1 + AnnualInterest, 1.0 / 2.0) - 1 Result = self.BillLine__BaseAmount * self.Power(1 + InterestOnPeriod, self.NumberOfMonthBetweenTwoDates(BeginDate, self.CurrentDate) / MonthOnSemiAnnual) - self.BillLine__BaseAmount else ; Annually InterestOnPeriod = AnnualInterest Result = self.BillLine__BaseAmount * self.Power(1 + InterestOnPeriod, self.NumberOfMonthBetweenTwoDates(BeginDate, self.CurrentDate) / MonthOnAnnual) - self.BillLine__BaseAmount endIf endIf endIf endIf endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
;Uses uses WFTypes ; Rule func Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State (State:tWFUSState):tWFNum8 var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.myowner).AppendParam(State, 0, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.myowner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') end endFunc
; Classification ; FieldDesc ; VarDesc
Proc WFCalculate(out Result :tWFAmountWithCalculatedCurrency) var returnString : CString var thecurrentDate : tWFDate var deathDate : tWFDate var daysBetween : Num8 var daysBetweenOnAYearBasis : Num8 var interestValue : Num8
deathDate = Death__DeathDate thecurrentDate = WF.GetFunctionalDate interestValue = Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State(Subscriber__PersonResidenceState) daysBetween = thecurrentDate - deathDate ; returnString = 'The Post Mortem Interest calculation was calculated using the interest rate of ' returnString = Concat(returnString, interestValue) returnString = Concat(returnString, ' over a period of ') returnString = Concat(returnString, daysBetween) returnString = Concat(returnString, ' day(s).') daysBetweenOnAYearBasis = daysBetween / 365 ; Result = DeliveredService__NetBenefitAmount * Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State(Subscriber__PersonResidenceState) * daysBetweenOnAYearBasis DeliveredService__AddInterestDetails(returnString, Result)
end

aWFRuleDesc.Name: Post-mortem interests

aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
Event of Death is a Suicide during the suicide exclusion period: Death benefit=return of the premium already paid on the policy Else Death benefit=Base face amount - Benefit already paid on the Accelerated Death benefit + Post Mortem Interest (interest from tthe date of death to the date of payment of the benefit)
Suicide exlusion period: This Policy does not cover suicide by the Primary Insured for two years after the Policy Date (in CO, and ND, within one year). In the event of suicide by the Primary Insured during that period, Our payment will be limited to a refund of all premiums paid for the Primary Insured's coverage.
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:2) (Implem Version:1)
class aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine)
uses WFCountryTypes, WFTypes, aWFRuleDesc, aWFDefaultAmountType
; Rule function Suicide_Exclusion_Period(ApplicationSignedStates : tWFUSState) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(ApplicationSignedStates, 0, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
; Classification ; FieldDesc ; VarDesc ; Indexes Of TableDesc procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : Num8) var PolicyAnniversaryDate : tWFDate var ExclPer : Num8 var Post_Mortem_Interest : Num8 var Number_of_Days : Num8 var Death_Benefit : Num8 var curdate : tWFDate var ABRAdministrationFees : Int8 var PaidPremiumToDay : tWFAmount
; Death benefit outside the exclusion period => Face amount on the Base ; - Benefit already Paid on the Accelerated Death benefit if any ; - $200,00 Administration Fees if any ; + Post Mortem Interest Death_Benefit = self.Coverage__CoverageAmountAtDate(self.Death__DeathDate) ABRAdministrationFees = 200 if self.DependentDelivered__AmountAlreadyPaid > 0 Death_Benefit -= (self.DependentDelivered__AmountAlreadyPaid + ABRAdministrationFees) endIf ; ;Number_of_Days = CurrentDate - Death__DeathDate ;Post_Mortem_Interest = Death_Benefit * Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State(Subscriber__PersonResidenceState) * (Number_of_Days / NumberOfDaysInCurrentYear) ; ;AppendComment(Concat('Post Mortem Interest : ', Post_Mortem_Interest)) ; ;Death_Benefit += Post_Mortem_Interest ; ; Event= suicide and inside the suicide exclusion period => return the premium already paid PolicyAnniversaryDate = self.Contract__ValidationDate PaidPremiumToDay = self.Contract__PaidPremiumToDay ExclPer = self.Suicide_Exclusion_Period(self.Subscriber__PersonResidenceState) self.IncYears(Int4(ExclPer), PolicyAnniversaryDate) ; if (self.Loss__Event = 'SUIC') and (self.Death__DeathDate < PolicyAnniversaryDate) self.AppendComment(Concat('Suicide - Return of premium: ', PaidPremiumToDay.type.AsCString(@PaidPremiumToDay))) Death_Benefit = self.Contract__PaidPremiumToDay endIf ; Result = Death_Benefit endProc

aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWLI_LifeDisabilityRuleEngine) (Def Version:1) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes, WFCountryTypes, aWFRuleDesc, WF
function Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State(State : tWFUSState) return tWFNum8 uses aWFStandAloneRule
var tmpRule : aWFRuleDesc
tmpRule = self.GetExactRuleToExecuteFromRankInRuleDesc(0, self.CurrentDate) if tmpRule <> Nil aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).AppendParam(State, 0, tmpRule) tmpRule.GetStandAloneResult(_Result, self) aWFStandAloneRule(tmpRule.MyOwner).CleanParamsAfterExecution(tmpRule) else self.AppendComment('No rule version defined at this date') endIf endFunc
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFAmountWithCalculatedCurrency) var returnString : CString var thecurrentDate : tWFDate var deathDate : tWFDate var daysBetween : Num8 var daysBetweenOnAYearBasis : Num8 var interestValue : Num8
deathDate = self.Death__DeathDate thecurrentDate = WF.GetFunctionalDate interestValue = self.Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State(self.Subscriber__PersonResidenceState) daysBetween = thecurrentDate - deathDate ; returnString = 'The Post Mortem Interest calculation was calculated using the interest rate of ' returnString = Concat(returnString, interestValue) returnString = Concat(returnString, ' over a period of ') returnString = Concat(returnString, daysBetween) returnString = Concat(returnString, ' day(s).') daysBetweenOnAYearBasis = daysBetween / 365 ; Result = self.DeliveredService__NetBenefitAmount * self.Post_Mortem_Interest_Rate_Per_State(self.Subscriber__PersonResidenceState) * daysBetweenOnAYearBasis self.DeliveredService__AddInterestDetails(returnString, Result) endProc

aWLILifeCapitalBenefit.TextualDescription: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil Arial;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}{\f2\fnil MS Sans Serif;}} {\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;} \viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang0\f0\fs20 Additional benefit payable for accidental death of the primary insured only.\par \par This rider automatically doubles the death benefit of your life insurance policy if the insurer die due to an accident.\par \par The following conditions must be satisfied:\par \pard\fi-195\li195\lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 The Insured must die as a direct result of accidental bodily injury and independently of any other causes and within ninety (90) days from the date of the injury;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 The Insured must die while the policy and this rider are in full force;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 The Insured must die before the policy anniversary nearest the Insured's 60th birthday; and\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 Satisfactory proof of death must be received at our Home Office.\par \pard\lang1036\f2\fs16\par \par \lang0\f0\fs20 We will not pay a Benefit if the Insured dies as a direct or indirect result of:\par \pard\fi-195\li195\lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 Suicide, or any attempt at suicide, while sane or insane;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 Bodily or mental infirmity or disease;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 Medical or surgical treatment;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 Travel or flight in or descent from any aircraft, except as a passenger with no duties aboard such aircraft while in flight;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 Service in the military, naval, or air forces of any country, combination of countries, or international organization while such country, combination of countries, or international organization is engaged in war; and War or any act of war. "War" means declared or undeclared war and includes resistance to armed aggression.\par \pard\lang1036\f2\fs16\par }

To reinstate the Base Policy, You must: \par \pard\fi-195\li195\lang1036\f1 -\lang1024\f2 \lang0\f0 request such reinstatement within five years following the date this Policy lapsed;\par \lang1036\f1 - \lang0\f0 pay all premiums for the Base Policy which would have been due if the Base Policy had never lapsed, with 7% interest per year, compounded annually;\par \pard\lang1036\f3\fs16\par \par \lang0\f0\fs20 The Primary Insured must be alive on the date We approve a reinstatement in order for that reinstatement to take effect. You cannot reinstate any coverage under this Policy after this Policy terminates.\par \par \par Any Riders, which have ended (lapsed) because a premium was not paid, may also be reinstated with the Base Policy. \par To reinstate such a Rider, You must: \par \pard\fi-195\li195\lang1024\f2\'b7\tab\lang0\f0 within five years following the date the Rider lapsed, complete a Request that it be reinstated; \par \pard\lang1024\f2\'b7\tab\lang0\f0 pay all premiums for that Rider which would have been due if that Rider had never lapsed, with 7% interest per year, compounded annually;\lang1036\f3\fs16\par }
